ZCZC EE40
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 222300 UTC
A LOW 992 LIES OVER THE ATLANTIC AT FIRST EXTENDING INTO THE FAR W. THROUGH
THE PERIOD THIS LOW PROGRESSES SLWY EWARDS BECMG CENTRED OVER IRISH SEA
BY THURSDAY AFTERNOON AND FLN TO 999. A SECOND LOW PRESSURE CENTRE 996 LIES
OVER SCANDINAVIA GRADUALLY MOV AWAY TO THE N-E. HIGH PRESSURE 1021 LIES
CENTRES W OF IBERIA THROUGHOUT. A SECOND HIGH PRESSURE CENTRE 1025 LIES S
OF ICELAND LOSING ITS IDENTITY ON TUESDAY MORNING. THROUGH MONDAY EVENING
STRG WINDS ASSOCIATED WITH THE FIRST LOW SPREAD INTO AREAS W OF 12 W AND
N OF 45 N. OVERNIGHT THESE WINDS SPREAD INTO AREAS W OF 06 W WITH NEAR
GALES IN SOLE AND SHANNON. BY TUESDAY EVENING WINDS RECEDE NWARDS BECMG
CONFINED N OF 50 N AND EXITING THE REGION THROUGH WEDNESDAY MORNING. FM
